# SDD Workflow — quick reference

This project uses a custom Spec-Driven Development workflow with three
personas (architect, developer, reviewer) coordinated through five slash
commands. Authoritative details live in `.cursor/commands/*.md`.

## Pipeline

````
/design feature-name
↓ (architect persona)
.cursor/specs/{feature}/
├── 00-global-spec.md
├── 00-technical-plan.md
├── tasks/NN-{layer}.md
└── status.md
↓
/build @.../tasks/NN-{layer}.md
↓ (developer persona — TDD with pytest)
status: ready for review
↓
/review
↓ (reviewer persona)
APPROVED → /build next task
CHANGES  → /build same task (fixing only flagged issues)
↓ (after all tasks done)
/review --commit (creates Conventional Commit)
```

## Commands

| Command | Persona | Effect |
|---------|---------|--------|
| `/design` | architect | Creates the four-file spec structure |
| `/build` | developer | Implements ONE task with TDD, stops |
| `/review` | reviewer | Audits last task, approves or returns issues |
| `/test` | none | Runs pytest suites independently |
| `/refactor` | none | Quality pass: ruff + mypy |

## Persona enforcement

Each command starts by loading `.cursor/skills/{role}/SKILL.md` and the
model must operate within that skill's boundaries:

- The architect does NOT write production code.
- The developer does NOT skip TDD or auto-advance to the next task.
- The reviewer does NOT modify source code.

## Spec structure (mandatory)

Every feature spec lives at `.cursor/specs/{feature-name}/` with:

- `00-global-spec.md` — what & why
- `00-technical-plan.md` — how (API, services, ports, structure)
- `tasks/NN-{layer}.md` — single-commit mini-specs (≤ 2h each)
- `status.md` — progress tracker

Default decomposition by layer:
01 Domain → 02 Application → 03 Infrastructure → 04 Integration.
Layers can be skipped (read-only feature with no domain changes) or split
(`02a-services.md`, `02b-events.md`).

## Architectural contract

All implementations follow `.cursor/rules/architecture.mdc`. The reviewer
enforces it.

Infrastructure → Application → Domain

| Operation | Component | Returns |
|-----------|-----------|---------|
| Use case | Service.execute() | DTO |
| Read (list) | Service.execute() | DTO with items list |

## Test execution by layer

| Layer touched | Tests |
|---------------|-------|
| `domain/` | `pytest -m unit` |
| `application/` | `pytest -m unit` |
| `infrastructure/persistence/` | `pytest -m "unit or integration"` |
| `infrastructure/api/` | `pytest -m "unit or integration or e2e"` |

Tests run inside the Docker container:
`docker compose exec backend uv run pytest -m {marker}`

## Quality gates

| Tool | Command | Required |
|------|---------|----------|
| ruff format | `uv run ruff format --check` | clean |
| ruff lint | `uv run ruff check` | clean |
| mypy | `uv run mypy src/` | clean (strict mode) |
| pytest | per layer (see above) | green |

## Definition of Done (per task)

A task is done when `/review` returns APPROVED:
1. Acceptance criteria from global spec covered
2. Implementation checklist in mini-spec completed
3. Tests for layer green
4. ruff format/check clean, mypy clean
5. Architectural checklist satisfied
6. `status.md` updated to `done`